==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prowess
<hw>Prow"ess</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>proece</ets>, <ets>proesce</ets>, F. <ets>prouesse</ets>. See
<er>Prow</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>Distinguished bravery; valor;
especially, military bravery and skill; gallantry; intrepidity;
fearlessness.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer. Sir P. Sidney.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He by his <qex>prowess</qex> conquered all France.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prowl</ent>⟦br⟧
